#: ../../../reference/routines.emath.rst:2
msgid "Mathematical functions with automatic domain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/routines.emath.rst:6
msgid ""
":mod:`numpy.emath` is a preferred alias for ``numpy.lib.scimath``, available "
"after :mod:`numpy` is imported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.emath:1
msgid ""
"Wrapper functions to more user-friendly calling of certain math functions "
"whose output data-type is different than the input data-type in certain "
"domains of the input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.emath:5
msgid ""
"For example, for functions like `log` with branch cuts, the versions in this "
"module provide the mathematically valid answers in the complex plane::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.emath:8
msgid ""
">>> import math\n"
">>> np.emath.log(-math.exp(1)) == (1+1j*math.pi)\n"
"True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.emath:12
msgid ""
"Similarly, `sqrt`, other base logarithms, `power` and trig functions are "
"correctly handled.  See their respective docstrings for specific examples."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.emath:16
msgid "Functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.emath:30:<autosummary>:1
msgid ":py:obj:`sqrt <numpy.emath.sqrt>`\\ \\(x\\)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.emath:30:<autosummary>:1
msgid "Compute the square root of x."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.emath:30:<autosummary>:1
msgid ":py:obj:`log <numpy.emath.log>`\\ \\(x\\)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.emath:30:<autosummary>:1
msgid "Compute the natural logarithm of `x`."
msgstr ""

